<div class="story">
<p>Fronting the Atlantic Ocean  and the Roanoke Sound, the &quot;Village at Nags Head&quot; is one of the few golf course communities on the Outer Banks. The Villages at Nags Head is a planned community consisting of 27 micro communities  including 
Duneridge Estates, Elliot Estates,
Oceanwatch, Seaside North,
Seaside South, Seawatch,
Seven Sisters, Sea Pointe,
Atlantic Watch, Baymeadow,
Captain's Watch on the oceanside and over on the westside spread around the golf course are Leeward Shores,
Linkside, Marsh Links,
The Masters, The Reflections,
The Ridges, Waters Edge, The 
Wedges and the new addition of Moon Gate. Each community has it's own Association Fee along with the association fee to the Village master association. This is why each little community has it's own personal landscaping which helps keep the entire Village good looking while allowing variations in how each community represents itself.</p>
 <p>Owners in the Village at Nags Head also have access to a number of amenities including the Nags Head Golf Links w/clubhouse, the Beach Club on the oceanfront w/ clubhouse, olympic sized pool, tennis, shuttle service, bar &amp; snack bar plus, over on the soundfront there is a pier and small beach for kayaking. The Village at Nags Head is located just south of the sounfront community of <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/nags head/old-nags-head-cove.asp" title="Old Nags Head Cove">Old Nags Head Cove</a>. </p>
